<TITLE> Markets fall on selling pressure </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sep 7 (bdnews24.com)Markets plunged for the second day in a row as selling pressure in the later part of the day caused the indices to fall. Dhaka Stock Exchange opened steady, with the benchmark index registering a gradual rise, before slumping in the midday session when the index neared the 3,000 point mark. The general index or DGEN closed on 2936.31, down 24.65 points or 0.83 percent, while the broader all share price index shed 22.04 points, or 0.88 percent, to finish at 2468.30. The blue chip DSE-20 closed at 2115.29, falling 17.77 points, or 0.83 percent. Market observers said the DGEN had crossed the 3,000 point level at least ten times over the last month, but had failed to sustain the mark. "As soon as the index reaches the mark, the market starts to fall. It seems the level creates panic among investors," said mutual fund operator Yaweer Sayeed. Meanwhile, turnover on the prime bourse slumped to Tk 4.97 billion from Tk 5.83 billion the previous day. More than 70 percent of the 240 shares traded on Monday lost value, with 183 declining, 51 advancing and six holding steady. Brokerage house officials said market bellwether, banks, eroded Sunday's gains, which mainly contributed to the fall. "However, all sectors lost with some scrips rising somewhat," an official of Lanka Bangla Securities told bdnews24.com. New entrant, Navana CNG, ended turnover leader, with shares of Tk 1.14 billion changing hands, surging 5.09 percent to close at Tk 214.40. Beximco followed with a turnover of Tk 444.758 million, crawling down 0.61 percent to Tk 275.30. Aftab Automobiles shot up 5.86 percent to Tk 1673.25, with a turnover of Tk 204.437 million. Bex Tex's turnover reached Tk 163.154 million, closing at Tk 60.20, slipping 0.98 percent Off-dock service provider Summit Alliance Port Ltd edged down 0.96 percent to Tk 2101.25, seeing Tk 150.591 million in turnover. Among other scrips on the turnover boardTitas Gas, AIMS 1st Mutual Fund and Jamuna Oil lost. Maksons Spinning Mills and IFIC Bank, however, rose. All indices on the Chittagong Stock Exchange also fell, led by losses in leasing & finance, banks and energy shares. The selective categories index or CSCX slumped 101.98 points, or 1.53 percent, to 6539. The all share price index or CASPI ended on 10326.89, losing 66.07 points, or 0.63 percent. The CSE-30 finished 27.95 points down, or 0.35 percent, at 7925.34. Turnover at the port city bourse stood at Tk 462.816 million through almost 4 million traded shares. Beximco Ltd topped the turnover board with shares of Tk 110.419 million changing hands. Beximco Pharma, Bex Tex, Navana CNG and AB Bank followed
